/* gamedata-w7-legend.mjs — Legend Talents (W7 account-wide talent tree, 50 IDs), extracted
 * verbatim from N.js. GENERATED by a one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed);
 * refresh after a major patch.
 *
 * WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: bonuses/thingies.mjs::legendPts()/gamedata.mjs's LEGEND_TALENT_COEFF only
 * had 10 of the 50 ids table-guarded (throws for the rest). This file supplies all 50 rows so
 * every talent can be shown/computed, not just the ones existing recipes happened to need.
 *
 * DISPATCHER: same `m._customBlock_Thingies` dispatcher as the other gamedata-w7-*.mjs files
 * (N.js byte 10698460). Legend cases at N.js byte ~10709420-10711100 (dumped and transcribed
 * end-to-end).
 *
 * LegendPTS_bonus(b), N.js byte ~10710880, verbatim (EXACTLY what bonuses/thingies.mjs already
 * implements — this file's LEGEND_TALENT_COEFF-equivalent, `coeff` below, is a superset of the
 * existing gamedata.mjs LEGEND_TALENT_COEFF; both were cross-checked against each other, 10/10
 * overlapping ids match EXACTLY, 0 mismatches):
 *   round(Spelunk[18][b] * CustomLists.LegendTalents[b][2])
 * Spelunk[18][b] = points the account has SPENT on talent b (savemap/w67.mjs does not document
 * Spelunk idx 18 — noted here as evidence for whoever owns that file next; confirmed via
 * LegendPTS_spent's own loop, see below).
 *
 * LegendPTS_spent(), N.js byte ~10709500, verbatim — confirms Spelunk[18] has exactly 50 slots:
 *   round(sum(Spelunk[18][e] for e in 0..49))
 *
 * LegendTalent_MaxLV(b), N.js byte ~10710430, verbatim — FOUR clusters of 5 talent ids each get
 * their max level linked to a specific Research Grid node's RAW LEVEL (Grid_Bonus(node,1), i.e.
 * ResearchStuff's "e==1" arm — see bonuses/research.mjs's header for what e==1 means), everyone
 * else just uses the table's flat maxLvBase:
 *   ids {2,13,3,18,5}    -> floor(Grid_Bonus(130,1) + LegendTalents[b][1])
 *   ids {9,23,33,1,16}   -> floor(Grid_Bonus(131,1) + LegendTalents[b][1])
 *   ids {20,31,19,27,8}  -> floor(Grid_Bonus(132,1) + LegendTalents[b][1])
 *   ids {34,30,29,6,26}  -> floor(Grid_Bonus(152,1) + LegendTalents[b][1])
 *   else                 -> LegendTalents[b][1]                          // = maxLvBase, flat
 * (Grid_Bonus(node,1) = Math.round(Research[0][node]), the node's raw save level — per
 * bonuses/research.mjs's own docstring. Nodes 130/131/132/152 are NOT in that file's
 * RES_GRID_COEFF, which only tracks nodes whose e==0 PERCENT bonus is consumed somewhere; these
 * four are consumed here via e==1 instead, a genuinely different use of the same node.)
 *
 * LEGEND_TALENTS — Ya.LegendTalents()=function(){return[...]}, N.js byte 14018010 (`return[` at
 * 14018042..14024882), 50 rows: ids 0-39 are REAL talents, ids 40-49 are literal `"filler"` rows
 * ("I_have_not_yet_considered_this_talent...", not yet implemented by the client) — EXCLUDED
 * from the array below (row-count gotcha: the save array Spelunk[18] is still 50 long, all 50
 * indices are valid to READ, but only 0-39 have real coeff/maxLV/name data). Columns:
 *   [0] name, [1] maxLvBase (LegendTalent_MaxLV's flat/base value), [2] coeff (LegendPTS_bonus's
 *   multiplier), [3] literal "filler" for every row including real ones — unused/reserved, same
 *   "always a constant no dispatcher reads" pattern as gamedata-w7-zenith.mjs's column [5],
 *   [4] short flavor label (`{`/`}`/`$`-templated), [5] long description.
 *
 * CROSS-CHECK vs gamedata.mjs's existing LEGEND_TALENT_COEFF (10 ids) — every one matches this
 * table's `coeff` column exactly, 0 mismatches: 1->500, 3->10, 5->10, 7->10, 8->100, 10->25,
 * 11->15, 19->75, 21->15, 24->20.
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

